<TITLE> Farm loan collection deferred in Aila-hit areas </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 1 (bdnews24.com) - The government has postponed agriculture loan collections from farmers in cyclone-hit areas. The decision came from a meeting at a cabinet meeting chaired by prime minister Sheikh Hasina, her press secretary said on Monday. The coastal regions have been reeling after in the wake cyclone Aila, which struck on May 25 and left over 150 dead. A total of 51 Upazila in 11 districts have seen losses of life, property and land, Azad said. Ministers were assigned in the cabinet to review aid work in the Aila-hit districts, he added. Health minister Ruhal Haque in Satkhira, state minister for religion Mohammad Shahjahan in Patuakhali, advisor to the prime minister Moshiur Rahman in Khulna and state minister for local government Jahangir Kabir Nanak in Barisal have been picked for the jobs. The disaster control room will be kept open round the clock for those seeking information in the wake of Aila, the prime minister's press secretary said. b
